Chinese first lady visits Tagore International School
2014-09-19 00:10:48 GMT
China’s first lady Peng Liyuan, wife of president Xi Jinping, visited Tagore International School in New Delhi in the afternoon of September 18.At the school, Peng helped the children with Chinese brush writing. She held the hand of a girl while showing her the right posture for writing, receiving warm applause.Before leaving the school, Peng was invited to take a group photo with the students and teachers. She said, after shaking hands with each of the teachers, “Teacher is a very respectable job. I’m a teacher, too.”Later children swarmed over for the group photo. Peng kept hugging them and even kissed some children on the face.Peng told the school president that the visit had left very beautiful memories for her, which she would always remember, particularly the smile of the children.She also invited the students and teachers to travel around in China:“I believe you will fall in love with China the moment you step on Chinese land. Let’s pass the friendship down together,” she said.Peng Liyuan arrived with her husband Xi Jinping in the western Indian city of Ahmedabad in Prime Minister Narendra Modi's home state of Gujarat on Wednesday, starting the three-day visit to the country. 
